NAF.raw: http : / / www . trust . org / item / ? map=plane - bombs - south - sudan - refugee - camp - witness / Plane bombs South Sudan refugee camp - witness Thu , 10 Nov 2011 02 : 45 PM A refugee camp was the target of an air strike in South Sudan's Unity state on Thursday , less than 50 km ( 30 miles ) from the tense border with Sudan , a Reuters witness said . There appeared to be no casualties . The Reuters correspondent heard a large explosion , then saw a crater about two metres ( 6 . 6 feet ) wide , an unexploded bomb wedged in the side of a school building and a white aircraft flying north from the Yida refugee camp . Witnesses at the camp said there were three other explosions at 3 p . m . ( 1200 GMT ) .
